 <text>
  <front>
   <head>THE EMPTY PURSE</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">What all despise, and all agree to curse,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I view with pride and joy, an Empty Purse.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When it was full, so was my heart of woe,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I knew not what to do, nor where to go.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I would be gen'rous, but I long'd for dress;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Appearing great, I made myself look less.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I that no kindred ever dar'd to claim;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Found fifty kind relations of my name.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No more could I complain of friends neglect,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And daring falsehood hung around my neck;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Amaz'd I cried, What means this mighty change;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The forward fool replied, 'Tis nothing strange.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Wretch, take my gold, I said, my greatest curse,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Leave me an honest heart, and empty purse.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
